  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (e3f14f6 2022-04-29T00:10:17.965855+00:00)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (M1)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nAfter creating the following directory structure:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ tree # edited output\r\n├── foundry.toml\r\n├── src\r\n│   └── try2.sol // imports \"dep/dep.sol\";\r\n├── lib\r\n│   ├── dep\r\n│   │   ├── foundry.toml // contains libs = ['lib2']\r\n│   │   ├── src\r\n│   │   │   └── dep.sol // imports \"dep2/dep2.sol\";\r\n│   │   ├── lib2\r\n│   │   │   ├── dep2\r\n│   │   │   │   ├── foundry.toml\r\n│   │   │   │   ├── src\r\n│   │   │   │   │   └── dep2.sol\r\n```\r\n\r\nRunning `forge build` in `./lib/dep` works; running `forge build` in `./` yields:\r\n```\r\n[⠒] Unable to resolve import: \"dep2/dep2.sol\" with remappings:\r\n        dep/=/Users/ah/foundry_issue/lib/dep/src/\r\n        ds-test/=/Users/ah/foundry_issue/lib/forge-std/lib/ds-test/src/\r\n        forge-std/=/Users/ah/foundry_issue/lib/forge-std/src/\r\n        src/=/Users/ah/foundry_issue/src/\r\n[⠆] Compiling 9 files with 0.8.13\r\n[⠰] Solc finished in 27.27ms\r\nError:\r\n   0: Compiler run failed\r\n      error[6275]: ParserError: Source \"dep2/dep2.sol\" not found: File not found. Searched the following locations: \"\".\r\n       --> /Users/ah/foundry_issue/lib/dep/src/dep.sol:1:1:\r\n        |\r\n      1 | import \"dep2/dep2.sol\";\r\n        | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n\r\n\r\n   0:\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   cli/src/compile.rs:149\r\n ```",
